parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front suspension can cause the vehicle to shake violently, leading to loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle shakes violently when hitting a bump or uneven road surface
especially at high speeds; the front end of the vehicle wobbles or oscillates; the steering wheel shakes or vibrates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cab mounts can cause the cab to bounce or shake, leading to loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The cab of the vehicle bounces or shakes excessively
especially when driving over bumps or uneven road surfaces.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose braking ability, leading to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The brakes fail to function properly
resulting in extended stopping distances or loss of control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering system can cause the vehicle to lose steering ability, leading to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The steering wheel shakes or vibrates excessively
especially when driving over bumps or uneven road surfaces.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front suspension can cause the vehicle to shake violently, making it difficult to control, and potentially leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle shakes violently when driving over bumps
at any speed. The steering wheel may move excessively from front to back and side to side
making it difficult to control the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering system can cause the vehicle to lose control, making it difficult to steer, and potentially leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: moves excessively from front to back and side to side
making it difficult to control the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the tire pressure monitoring system can cause the vehicle to lose control, making it difficult to steer, and potentially leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The tire pressure monitoring system fails to alert the driver of low tire pressure
which can cause the vehicle to shake violently or lose control.
